\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Κορνήλιος\"><span data-text=\"Κορνήλιος\" data-n=\"25\" data-lemma=\"Κορνήλιος\">ΚΟΡΝΗΛΙΟΣ</span></span>·<span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ἀγα\n                    θήμερος\"><span data-text=\"Ἀγα\n                    θήμερος\" data-n=\"35\" data-lemma=\"Ἀγαθήμερος\">ΑΓΑ<br id=\"al3-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span>ΘΗΜΕΡΟΣ</span></span></span>·<span data-text=\"ἐζη·\n                    σεν\" data-n=\"45\" data-lemma=\"ζάω\">ΕΖΗ- ·<br id=\"al4-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span>ΣΕΝ</span><span data-text=\"ἔτη\" data-n=\"55\" data-lemma=\"ἔτος\">ΕΤΗ</span>·<span data-text=\"XXXVIII\" data-n=\"65\" data-lemma=\"XXXVIII\">XXXVIII</span><br id=\"al5-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">5</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Εὐφροσύνη\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Εὐφροσύνη\"><span data-text=\"Εὐφροσύνη\" data-n=\"70\" data-lemma=\"Εὐφροσύνη\">ΕΥΦΡΟΣΥΝΗ</span></span></span>·<span data-text=\"ἰδίῳ\" data-n=\"80\" data-lemma=\"ἴδιος\">ΙΔΙΩ</span><span data-text=\"συν\n                    βίῳ\" data-n=\"85\" data-lemma=\"σύμβιος\">ΣΥ<span class=\"small\" title=\"small character: ν\">Ν</span><br id=\"al6-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">6</span>ΒΙΩ</span><span data-text=\"μνήμης\" data-n=\"90\" data-lemma=\"μνήμη\">ΜΝΗΜΗΣ</span><span data-text=\"χάριν\" data-n=\"95\" data-lemma=\"χάριν\">ΧΑΡΙΝ</span></span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Victoria Fendel, Robert Crellin</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic-simple-lemmatized\"><div class=\"textpart\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><span data-text=\"Θεοῖς\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"θεός\">ΘΕΟΙΣ</span><span data-text=\"Καταχθονίοις\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"καταχθόνιος\">ΚΑΤΑΧΘΟΝΙΟΙΣ</span><span data-text=\"Κορνήλιος\" data-n=\"25\" data-lemma=\"Κορνήλιος\">ΚΟΡΝΗΛΙΟΣ</span><span data-text=\"Ἀγαθήμερος\" data-n=\"35\" data-lemma=\"Ἀγαθήμερος\">ΑΓΑΘΗΜΕΡΟΣ</span><span data-text=\"ἐζησεν\" data-n=\"45\" data-lemma=\"ζάω\">ΕΖΗΣΕΝ</span><span data-text=\"ἔτη\" data-n=\"55\" data-lemma=\"ἔτος\">ΕΤΗ</span><span data-text=\"XXXVIII\" data-n=\"65\" data-lemma=\"XXXVIII\">XXXVIII</span><span data-text=\"Εὐφροσύνη\" data-n=\"70\" data-lemma=\"Εὐφροσύνη\">ΕΥΦΡΟΣΥΝΗ</span><span data-text=\"ἰδίῳ\" data-n=\"80\" data-lemma=\"ἴδιος\">ΙΔΙΩ</span><span data-text=\"συνβίῳ\" data-n=\"85\" data-lemma=\"σύμβιος\">ΣΥΝΒΙΩ</span><span data-text=\"μνήμης\" data-n=\"90\" data-lemma=\"μνήμη\">ΜΝΗΜΗΣ</span><span data-text=\"χάριν\" data-n=\"95\" data-lemma=\"χάριν\">ΧΑΡΙΝ</span></span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2><a href=\"ISic001308_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"Photo by students of Liceo M.M. Lazzaro, Catania\" src=\"ISic001308_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic001308.jpg\"><img title=\"Photo by students of Liceo M.M. Lazzaro, Catania\" src=\"ISic001308-thumb.jpg\"></a></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span>  <span>text from photograph</span>  </span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>English translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\"><a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag</a></p>  <p>To the gods of the underworld. Kornelios Agathemeros lived 38 years. Euphrosyne (set this up) as a memorial for her own partner in life.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>Italian translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\">Serena Agodi</p>  <p>Agli dèi del mondo sotterraneo. Kornelios Agathemeros ha vissuto 38 anni. Eufrosia (lo pose) a ricordo del proprio compagno di vita.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p> This epitaph was found together with ISic001314 (inv. no.272), which was apparently erected by the same man as is commemorated in this text (although it is also possible that they are father and son). The implication is that Euphrosyne was his second wife, who outlived him. The use of Latin numerals in the middle of the Greek text is a clear indication of the co-existence of the two languages in Catania at this date and the ‘interference’ between them (just as the name Cornelius Agathemeros combines Latin and Greek names also).</p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> Franz 1853 5695 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250</a>  </li><li> Kaibel 1890 <a href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">485</a>  <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072</a>  </li><li> Korhonen 2004 73 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028</a>  </li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"> Line 1  12-25  Interlineation line 1 to 2  not measured  </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.  </div>",
